meta_keywords: Office of Policy Planning and Coordination on Territory and Sovereignty
Tottori Prefecture Fisheries Research Institute Operations for FY1932 & FY1933
data.meta_description: A report on mackerel longline fishing trials carried out in sea areas between Utsuryo Island (Ulleungdo) and Takeshima in June-July 1932 and May-June 1933.
data.text: The uninhabited island, Takeshima (Liancourt Rocks) located approximately 80 nautical miles northwest of Oki Province. Its circumstance is approximately 4km, and when east or west wind blows, at least several boats of less than 30 tons can drop their anchors. In addition, it is the most appropriate place for the Prefecture to use as a base to go fishing to the area near Utsuryo Island (Ulleungdo). The survey such like above was conducted.
